vllm-shim local patch: synthesize fused exclude entries in Quark
config so layers HF-named gate_proj / up_proj that should be skipped
also match SGLang's fused gate_up_proj.

SGLang fuses gate_proj + up_proj into a single gate_up_proj linear
during model build. Quark checkpoints (Kimi K2.6 MXFP4 etc.) ship
their "exclude" list using the original HF unfused names. Without
synthesizing the fused names here, layers the checkpoint marks as
quantization-skipped (the MoE expert gate/up, the NextN eh_proj, etc.)
fall back to the quantized path because `should_ignore_layer(prefix,
ignore=self.exclude_layers, ...)` does not see a matching name and
returns False. The result on the user side is either silent garbage
output or a load-time shape error depending on the layer.

We patch QuarkConfig.from_config (the only construction site that
resolves the exclude list) rather than the per-layer match, so the
synthesis is one-shot at model init and downstream call sites stay
unchanged. Deduped via dict.fromkeys so callers that already provide
fused names in the original config see no duplicates.

Adapted from prior MXFP4 + MI300X work; no upstream PR.

--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/quark/quark.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/quark/quark.py
@@ -164,6 +164,19 @@
             if q_proj_q_config is not None:
                 q_proj_q_config["output_tensors"] = None
-
+        # Synthesize fused exclude entries: SGLang fuses gate_proj+up_proj
+        # into gate_up_proj at model build, but Quark exclude lists use HF
+        # unfused names. Without this synthesis the fused linear escapes
+        # the exclude list and gets quantized despite the checkpoint asking
+        # for it to stay in BF16.
+        excludes = cast(list[str], config.get("exclude", []))
+        additions: list[str] = []
+        for e in excludes:
+            if ".gate_proj" in e:
+                additions.append(e.replace(".gate_proj", ".gate_up_proj"))
+            if ".up_proj" in e:
+                additions.append(e.replace(".up_proj", ".gate_up_proj"))
+        config["exclude"] = list(dict.fromkeys(excludes + additions))
+
         return cls(
             quant_config=config,
             kv_cache_group=kv_cache_group,
